FBIS3-28134 "dreas023_d_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-023 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Feb 1994 South Korea DPRK Reportedly Rejects Nuclear Inspections `Total Rejection' of Inspections SK0302025094 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0230 GMT 3 Feb 94 SK0302025094 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Text] North Korea today officially informed the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] of its total rejection [chonmyon kobu] of nuclear inspections. Meanwhile, U.S. Defense Secretary-nominee Perry said that in the event that dialogue between North Korea and the IAEA is suspended and the IAEA declares that the continuity of North Korea's nuclear safeguard measures is broken [kkaejida], the United States will immediately refer the North Korean nuclear issue to the UN Security Council.
